text.paragraph:
ACIPHEX in combination with amoxicillin and clarithromycin as a 
three drug regimen, is indicated for the treatment of patients with H. pylori infection and duodenal ulcer disease (active or 
history within the past 5 years) to eradicate H. 
pylori. Eradication of H. pylori has been 
shown to reduce the risk of duodenal ulcer recurrence. {See CLINICAL STUDIES (
                              14.5
                           ) and DOSAGE AND 
ADMINISTRATION (
                              2.5
                           )}

list.item:
History of hypersensitivity to rabeprazole (
                                 4.1
                              )

Rabeprazole has been shown to inhibit cyclosporine metabolism in vitro (
                                 7.3
                              )

ACIPHEX may reduce the plasma levels of atazanavir (
                                 7.4
                              )
